<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JUL 93 / TUC calls for Hanson council
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A SENIOR TUC official yesterday called for a world-wide trade union council
to bring together representatives of workers employed by Hanson Corporation.
Mr David Lea, TUC assistant general secretary, made the call at a rally to
support miners on strike against the Hanson subsidiary Peabody, the biggest
coal producer in the USA.
