FT  15 JUL 93 / US-North Korean talks 'useful'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Senior US and North Korean officials held seven hours of talks in Geneva
yesterday in a second attempt to head off confrontation over Pyongyang's
refusal to allow international inspection of suspect nuclear sites, writes
Frances Williams in Geneva. Mr Robert Gallucci, US assistant secretary of
