not only see the house but also the extensive country park, the stunning
gardens and grounds and the museums (including a motor museum).
At both places he could have enjoyed a cup of tea and a meal. He could have
bought granny a souvenir and at Sandringham the children could have tried
the adventure playground.
What more does he want?
E F Grove,
