<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 93 / India posts 30% jump in exports
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SHIRAZ SIDHVA
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW DELHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
India's exports recorded a 30 per cent growth to reach Dollars 3.46bn
(Pounds 2.34bn) in April and May, the first two months of the current fiscal
year, against Dollars 2.67bn in the corresponding period of last year,
writes Shiraz Sidhva in New Delhi.
Official statistics yesterday showed imports fell 4.05 per cent to Dollars
3.47bn compared with Dollars 3.61bn. The country's trade deficit has fallen
to Dollars 6.59m against Dollars 944.7m last year.
