<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUL 93 / Iraqi regime prepares for further US strikes
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Middle East Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
IRAQ yesterday began to prepare the public for possible US military attacks,
following its refusal to let United Nations weapons inspectors seal off two
missile sites west of Baghdad pending installation of remote-control
cameras.
Mr Rolf Ekeus, head of the UN weapons inspection team, flew to Bahrain
yesterday on his way to Baghdad in what is likely to be the final attempt to
