</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China's metal industry is the latest state-owned operation to announce a big
restructuring, promising to cut 330,000 jobs during the next seven years,
Reuter reports from Beijing.
But few if any of the workers to be laid off by the China National
Nonferrous Metals Industry Corp (CNNC) will end up jobless, the China Daily
said yesterday. 'Workers made redundant are to be re-employed in service
industries and other profitable businesses set up under collective ownership
by CNNC's subsidiaries,' the official newspaper said.
