Primary Aluminium Institute's announcement of a 50,000-tonne rise in
producer stocks in May, which reinforced bearish pressure. The three months
price closed at Dollars 1,217.50 a tonne, down Dollars 27 on the day, taking
it below the level ruling two weeks ago when Aluminum Company of America
sparked an upturn with the announcement of plans for substantial production
cuts. Dealers said disappointment at the failure of other producers to
follow Alcoa's lead had eroded the constructive impact of that move.
