2.2-litre engine beginning in mid-1994.
The blocks, destined for Toyota Camrys built in Georgetown, Kentucky, will
be produced at GM's Defiance, Ohio, facility. GM said it would provide
180,000 blocks annually for the 16-valve engines.
GM said the agreement was part of a strategy to expand the business to
secure jobs for General Motors and United Auto Workers-represented
employees.
GM Powertrain's plant in Defiance manufactures grey iron and nodular iron
castings and employs 3,773.
