acquisition of new technologies, product development and publishing of new
catalogues. Operating expenses were up to Dollars 1.07m (Dollars 858,000)
against sales virtually unchanged at Dollars 3.58m.
The measures taken were beginning to impact positively. 'We look forward to
a strong first half', Mr Denton said.
First quarter shipments were 'comfortably ahead' but orders booked were
running more than 40 per cent over a year ago.
Earnings per share came through at 0.7 cents (1.4 cents).
